# ==========================================================================
# Portrait privacy fence — ship the METHOD, never the person.
# ==========================================================================
#
# SCHEME (template-vs-live):
#   *.template.md   → TRACKED. The shippable method: format, seeds, placeholders.
#                     Zero personal content. This is what other people clone.
#   live files      → IGNORED. The user's actual filled-in portrait. Local-only.
#                     Created by copying a *.template.md to its live name and
#                     filling the placeholders. Never committed, never auto-leaves
#                     the machine (local-first rule, CLAUDE.md Privacy & guardrails).
#
# HOW TO GO LIVE (per file):
#   cp identity/PORTRAIT.template.md            identity/PORTRAIT.md
#   cp identity/portraits/_PORTRAIT_001.template.md  identity/portraits/_PORTRAIT_001.md
#   cp identity/disputed.template.md            identity/disputed.md
#   cp identity/sources.template.md             identity/sources.md
# Then fill. The live copies below are ignored; the .template.md originals stay tracked.
#
# RULE: anything containing real corpus content, inferences about the user, or
# real local paths is LIVE and must match a pattern below. If you add a new
# live artifact type, add its ignore line here in the same commit.
# ==========================================================================

# --- live portrait (the synthesized "current" portrait) ---
identity/PORTRAIT.md

# --- live frozen snapshots (the dated gallery) ---
# Ignore every real snapshot; the *.template.md seed stays tracked (negation below).
identity/portraits/*.md
!identity/portraits/*.template.md

# --- live anti-Barnum feedback log ---
identity/disputed.md

# --- live corpus manifest (contains real local paths) ---
identity/sources.md

# --- live semantic-recall index (holds real corpus content) ---
# Built by recall/recall.py; vectors + source chunks of the personal corpus.
# Local-only. The METHOD (recall/recall.py + recall/requirements.txt) is tracked;
# the index is not.
identity/recall.db
identity/recall.db-shm
identity/recall.db-wal

# --- local embedding-model cache (downloaded ONNX weights, ~130 MB) ---
recall/.model_cache/

# macOS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
